      dek: `Color is the final layer of storytelling — the stage where raw footage becomes a film with a look. Grading isn't just "making it pretty"; it's shaping mood, guiding the eye, and giving your whole film a visual identity. It's one of the most powerful tools you have, and one of the most misunderstood.`,
